com.microfocus.adm.pulse.pluginapi.chain

Interface PulseFindingBuilder


  • public interface PulseFindingBuilder

    Used to create findings that will be recorded using PulseFindingReporter. Findings describe issues discovered by an expert about items in a changeset.

    The same builder can be used to create multiple findings, allowing for an expert to generate all the findings for the same item by setting the path on this builder and the varying the other properties. This will mean that PulseFinding returned from build() will all have the same path value.

    Each property setter returns this builder allowing property calls to be chained together, e.g. builder.path("/src/main.java").line(10).message("Unreachable code").build()

    Since:
    19.1.1

      • build

        PulseFinding build()

        Create a new PulseFinding using the current properties of this builder.

        Returns:
        New PulseFinding. Can not be null.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - thrown if the PulseFinding state would be invalid.
        Since:
        19.1.1

      • type

        PulseFindingBuilder type(PulseFindingType type)

        Set the type of finding to build. By default the builder will create PulseFindingType.FILE findings. Changing the finding type will not reset the path or line number for the builder but if the type does not need them, they will be ignored when the finding is built.

        Parameters:
        type - Type of finding to build.
        Returns:
        This builder to allow chaining.
        Since:
        19.1.1

      • path

        PulseFindingBuilder path(String path)

        Set the path the finding relates to. The path is always the "after" path for the associated change in the changeset. A path must be provided to successfully build a PulseFindingType.FILE or PulseFindingType.LINE finding. Attempting to build a finding for those types with no path will result in an IllegalStateException being thrown by the build() method.

        Parameters:
        path - Path of the change the finding is associated with.
        Returns:
        This builder to allow chaining.
        Since:
        19.1.1

      • line

        PulseFindingBuilder line(int line)

        Set the line number the finding relates to. If the finding is a PulseFindingType.FILE or PulseFindingType.LINE, the line number is not required and will be ignored. The line number defaults to 0.

        Parameters:
        line - Line number the finding was found on.
        Returns:
        This builder to allow chaining.
        Since:
        19.1.1

      • label

        PulseFindingBuilder label(String label)

        Set the label for the message. This will be displayed with the message within the user interface and can be something that identifies the message, i.e. a compiler error number or a security alert reference.

        Parameters:
        label - String version of the label.
        Returns:
        This builder to allow chaining.
        Since:
        19.1.1

      • message

        PulseFindingBuilder message(String message)

        Set the message that will be displayed to Pulse users for this finding. A message must be provided to successfully build a finding. Attempting to build a finding with no message will result in an IllegalStateException being thrown by the build() method.

        Parameters:
        message - String that describes the finding in a human readable way.
        Returns:
        This builder to allow chaining.
        Since:
        19.1.1

      • severity

        PulseFindingBuilder severity(PulseFindingSeverity severity)

        Set the severity of the finding. Severity of findings default to PulseFindingSeverity.INFO.

        Parameters:
        severity - Severity of the finding
        Returns:
        This builder to allow chaining.
        Since:
        19.1.1
